{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage audit — parent safe-luge-nog/b4d4-3369-6dd2-41e6, THIS child (ba2c parent-CLEAR consumer) vs whole roster (908c link-consumer + ba2c parent-consumer)]\n\n4-bucket audit of parent SC/AC, each flagged absence cross-checked against the WHOLE roster:\n\n- SC1 (provider-agnostic primitive consumed by BOTH parent + link removal, no Jira logic in gate): FULLY (joint) — ba2c consumes the gate on the PARENT CLEAR path (CLEAR emitted only when Jira parent ∈ managed_refs; never-managed parent ADOPTED), 908c on the LINK path. Both halves present; ba2c AC4 affirms \"parent + link removal share the same gate helper (no duplicated provenance logic).\"\n- AC1 (reducer folds managed_refs: monotonic, sorted, never reduced by UNLINK): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope retains \"the reducer managed_refs field + compaction preservation + byte-parity\" as its OWN in-scope primitive work; consumers only READ the set. Not delegated to children → not a child-attributable gap.\n- AC2 (absent managed_refs → seed from deps+parent_id; pre-feature-compacted test): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope retains \"migration-seeding.\"\n- AC3 (survives compact_ticket; compact-then-reconcile test): COVERED behaviorally on consumer paths — ba2c AC3 \"incl. across a compaction boundary\" (parent kind) + 908c AC5 \"survives a compaction boundary\" (link kind); restore mechanism (process_snapshot) is parent-side.\n- AC4 (SNAPSHOT byte-parity / deterministic serialization): STRUCTURAL — parent-owned serialization.\n- AC5 (shared should_propagate_removal exists, provider-agnostic, defaults empty→False, unit-tested REMOVE-vs-ADOPT): gate existence + its own unit tests are STRUCTURAL (parent Scope: \"the shared provider-agnostic gate helper with its own unit tests\"); the REMOVE-vs-ADOPT DECISION is additionally exercised jointly through consumers — ba2c (managed parent → CLEAR; never-managed parent → ADOPT, regression test) + 908c (managed link → REMOVE; never-managed → ADOPT). Covered.\n- AC6 (operator-facing regression: unlink a managed ref, two reconcile passes, stays removed): COVERED (joint) — 908c AC5 \"local-unlink of a managed link emits an outbound remove and is not re-added inbound\" is the churn-fixed regression for the LINK kind; ba2c covers the PARENT kind (human-set parent adopted not cleared; managed parent CLEAR converges).\n- AC7 (docs/ documents pattern + future reclamation hook as template): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope retains \"docs establishing the reusable pattern.\"\n\nAbsence cross-check: every parent criterion is either (a) jointly covered by the two named CONSUMERS (SC1, AC3 durability, AC5 decision, AC6 regression) or (b) parent-owned in-scope primitive-build work the Scope deliberately retains rather than delegating (AC1, AC2, AC4, gate unit-tests, AC7 docs). This container is a primitive-building story that carves reducer/seeding/byte-parity/gate-helper/docs into its OWN scope and tracks only the two consumer integrations as children. THIS child (parent-CLEAR consumer) fully covers its half; sibling 908c covers the link half. No uncovered parent criterion is attributable to the children.\n\nResult: G3 CLEAN (empty findings)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782537724489153001,"uuid":"882af51a-6520-45c8-8016-c20dc3c11159"}